# AVD-AWS-0017: CloudWatch log groups not encrypted with a customer-managed KMS key.
# AWS-managed encryption is enabled by default and is sufficient for this workload.
# A CMK would add operational overhead (key rotation, IAM policies) with no meaningful
# security benefit for transient application logs.
AVD-AWS-0017

# AVD-AWS-0025: DynamoDB table not encrypted with a customer-managed KMS key.
# AWS-managed SSE is explicitly enabled (server_side_encryption.enabled = true).
# A CMK is not required for this workload's threat model.
AVD-AWS-0025

# AVD-AWS-0090: S3 bucket versioning not enabled.
# Reports are deterministically regenerated on every request; versioning adds S3 storage
# cost without providing recovery value. Tracked for future evaluation in the README.
AVD-AWS-0090

# AVD-AWS-0132: S3 bucket access logging not enabled.
# Object access is gated exclusively via short-lived presigned URLs; S3 server-access logs
# are not required. Can be enabled when access auditing becomes a requirement.
AVD-AWS-0132
